d with the fact if you fart the spell breaks makes it pretty worthless.  I doubt many druids or shaman are even familiar with it.  Seriously, they should make the duration unlimited.  Then at least it would be useful to move mules around or something. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=naloniusistari>Nalonius Istari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 149<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/3/03 8:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: useless spell</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>It might be of minor use if you can cast this on Xuzl, but since it dies nearly instantly from any real attack I can't see where that would be any value either<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
  Actually, you can keep one Xuzl around for a very very long time if your doing it right.<br>
<br>
  You need a tank that really good gaining agro as part of your group, my fav is a Paladin that uses Flash of Light (And the only tank I trust to keep me alive when someone calls for a full burn incidentally, Flash is stupid good for agro). You do all the pulling. First mob, get Xuzl out there, and buff it. Go pull next mob while that one is still around with whatever nuke you happen to be using to do damage, and run it close to camp. Root it, walk up and let it hit you once. Repeat. As long a mob is standing that has hit you, Xuzl will stick around.<br>
<br>
 Granted, I haven't bothered to try this in some time. Can anyone confirm it still works this way?<br>
<br>
