<br>
FoL: I have a lil pally alt I play with my gf's cleric and some other RL friends on the occasion. FoL is awesome strip material. Mob strips to the cleric, I run up behind, taunt, FoL, bash, stun, etc. It is usually on me once the FoL hits, and she can back up.<br>
<br>
HOWEVER, mobs WILL strip even when blind. The mob wants to stay on someone in melee, but if someone out of melee gains enough aggro it will (and has) stripped away from me. It then runs around doing the &quot;I'm blind&quot; dance. No, I was not out of range, and this has happened on two occasions where I know it was truly stripping: right after receiving a big heal, or when the cleric moves away before I have aggro (read: I'm swinging and making contact, but its still aggro'd on her... she moves away, it runs around blind instead of just switching to me or running straight for her).<br>
<br>
Sense the dead: awesome for harvesting bone chips in a newbie yard<br>
<br>
My vote is with the sanctuary/sentinel spells. I'm really not even sure what their intended purpose is, and I've tried, heh <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=596996" target="top">Infirno</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
